IndicateAdjustmentPresetsCreatesLayers.Content:
Each Adjustment preset creates a group with adjustment layers. By clicking the properties icon on each layer, you can edit the sliders for each part of the effect.

To remove a preset, you can click Revert in the Adjust panel or delete the layer group in the Layers panel.

IndicateQuickActionsCreateLayers.Content:
Each Quick action creates a layer in the Layers panel. To hide or show your effect, you can toggle the layer visibility ('eye' icon).

To remove your effect, you can use the Revert button in the Quick actions panel or delete the layer in the Layers panel.
IndicateQuickActionsCreateLayers.Title: Quick actions create layers
